[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["NZ default banner.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.wises.co.nz\/l\/seddon\/‎ ",{"type":"'''","value":["Seddon"]}]}," is a town in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Marlborough (New Zealand)"]]}," near the mouth of the Awatere River.  Until the grape boom, Seddon's farmers struggled farming sheep on dry hills.  Now you will struggle to find a sheep in amongst the vineyards.  Named after Richard John Seddon, Premier of New Zealand 1893-1906.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By car"]},"\nTravelling north, ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Blenheim (New Zealand)"],["Blenheim"]]}," is 15 minutes from Seddon on State Highway 1 (SH1).  ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Picton (New Zealand)"],["Picton"]]}," is a further 20min. South of Seddon is ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Ward"]]}," (15min), ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kaikoura"]]}," (1.25h) and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Christchurch"]]}," (4h).\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By bus"]},"\nAll ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Christchurch"]]}," - ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Picton (New Zealand)"],["Picton"]]}," ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.intercitycoach.co.nz buses"]}," and shuttles ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.atomictravel.co.nz Atomic"]},", ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.kahurangi.co.nz Kahurangi"]}," stop in Seddon.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\nThe ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.kiwirailscenic.co.nz\/coastal-pacific\/ ",{"type":"'''","value":["Coastal Pacific"]}]},", +64 4 495-0775 (",{"type":"''","value":["email bookings@kiwirailscenic.co.nz, fax +64 4 472 8903, Freephone 0800 TRAINS (0800 872 467) (NZ only)"]},") runs between ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Christchurch"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Picton (New Zealand)"],["Picton"]]}," daily from October to April. It will stop in Seddon on request.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" Take a drive out to the coast - there is vast swathes of grape vines as well as access to the wild shore with sweeping views up and down the coast."]},{"type":"*","value":[" One of the few double decker bridges in the world, the top deck with rail and the bottom with road traffic has just been taken out of commission.  Just north of Seddon on SH1. First opened to traffic in 1902, the rail portion remains now that the new road bridge is completed.  The old roadway has been removed."]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["do"],["name=Molesworth Tour Company"],["url=http:\/\/www.molesworthtours.co.nz\/"],["email=info@molesworthtours.co.nz"],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone = +64 3 577 9897"],["tollfree="],["fax=+64 3 577 9895"],["hours="],["price="],["content= A backcountry experience."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["do"],["name=Awatere Golf Club"],["url="],["email="],["address=State Highway 1"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone = +64 3 575 7072"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Cosy Corner Cafe"],["alt=Starborough Tearooms"],["url="],["email="],["address=State Highway 1"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone = +64 3 575 7285"],["tollfree="],["fax=03 575 7085"],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["drink"],["name=Starborough Tavern"],["url="],["email="],["address=23 Goulter Street"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone = +64 3 575 7006"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Sleep"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Awatere Motor Camp"],["url="],["email=awaterecom@xtra.co.nz"],["address=Seymour Street, Seddon Domain"],["lat="]